# Release curation — <PROJECT>

Read by the release pipeline when drafting the **client** release note. It carries routing,
not judgement: what the client can see, what they call it, and what must never leave the
building. The judgement — what actually matters this release, and what to leave out — is the
human's, every time.

Owner: whoever runs the release.

> **This file is incomplete on purpose.** The sections marked TODO are the ones nobody can
> infer from the codebase — they are how the client speaks, not how the system is built. The
> pipeline is instructed to _ask_ rather than guess, so leaving a TODO here is safe. Guessing
> is what is not.

