## Client-visible

Work under these paths is a candidate for the client note. Being here does not make it a
story — it makes it worth _considering_.

**TODO — list the paths the client actually sees or operates.** For example:

- `app/**` / `frontend/**` — the pages and flows they use
- `.../api/**` — new capability exposed to the app
- worker/background paths — only where they change what the client observes

## Internal only

Real work. Not a client story. Keep it in `CHANGELOG.md`.

- `test/**`, `.github/**`, `scripts/**`
- Refactors, dependency bumps, CI, lint, type fixes
- Anything whose value is "the code is now easier to work on"

## Operational notes → the technical changelog, never the client note

Migrations that need a manual apply, new environment variables, and anything that changes how
prod is deployed. That belongs in `CHANGELOG.md` where an engineer will look for it — not in a
document being handed to the client.

## Never leaves the building

Fed to the REDACT gate as extra patterns, on top of its built-in credential deny-list. One
per line, plain substrings.

**TODO — add the shared-infra identifiers and internal system names for this project.**
Database/project ids, service hostnames, third-party system names, internal API-key env-var
names. The credential deny-list is built in on top of this — these are the project-specific
terms it cannot know about.
